{
  "id": 5073321259565056,
  "name": "side-relative syntax for background-position-x/y longhands",
  "summary": "Defines the background image's position relative to one of its edges. \n\nThis syntax gives web authors a more flexible and responsive mechanisms to define the background image position, instead of using fixed values that need to be adapted to the window's or frame's size. \n\nThis feature is applied also to the \"-webkit-mask-position\" to ensure webcompat levels are the same.",
